oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Aerial view of farm
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: An aerial view of Clifton Place, home of Mr. W. P. Ridley near Mount Pleasant, Tenn. The image shows various barns and pasture located on the estate as well as the Mansions and the roads.
Built by Nathan Vaught. Clifton place was the first of three mansions on the land.
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:source: Tennessee Department of Conservation Photograph Collection, 1937-1976
